<HEAD>

<TITLE>COMMISSIONERS TO APPEAR ON
C-SPAN -- TRC
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<center><i>OCTOBER 18, 1995</i>
<P>
<h3>TAX REFORM COMMISSIONERS TO APPEAR ON
C-SPAN VIEWER CALL-IN, MONDAY, OCTOBER 23
</CENTER>

<P>
 <blockquote>Taxpayers from across America will have an opportunity
to discuss tax reform with members of the National Commission
and Economic Growth and Tax Reform during a nationally televised
viewer call-in program next week.
<P>
 The program will air, live, from 9:00 a.m. until
10:00 a.m. EST, on Monday, October 23, 1995, on C-Span.  Brian
Lamb, the network's founder and CEO, will moderate the show.
<P>
 During the program, viewers can ask questions of
Tax Reform Commissioners Herman Cain, Chairman and CEO of Godfather's
Pizza, and Jack Faris, President of the National Federation of
Independent Business (NFIB).  Jack Kemp, Chairman of the Tax Reform
Commission, will lead-off the program with an unedited pre-recorded
interview.
<P>
 The 14-member Tax Reform Commission was appointed
by Senate Majority Leader Bob Dole and House Speaker Newt Gingrich
earlier this year, and charged with making recommendations for
a tax code that will encourage economic growth and greater opportunity
for all Americans.  
<P>
 The Commission recently completed a series of public
hearings across the country, 12 in all, where some 120 witnesses
testified.  Among those were citizens representing family farms,
inner city business, the high-tech community, academia, small
businesses, large manufacturers, government entities, and Wall
Street.
<P>
 The Tax Reform Commission expects to issue its final
recommendations in early 1996.
</blockquote><P>


<P><P><font size="-1"><a href="/taxcom/prindex.html">PR Index</a> | <a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> | <a href="/taxcom/reptoc.html">The Report</a></font></center><P></body>

