<HEAD>

<TITLE>Cleveland Meeting Announced -- TRC
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<center>
<i>September 26, 1995</i>
<P>
<h3>NATIONAL TAX REFORM COMMISSION TO HOLD CLEVELAND
HEARING</h3>
</CENTER>


<CENTER>
<blockquote><I>Chairman Jack Kemp, Ohio State Treasurer Blackwell,
Farm Bureau President Kleckner to hear citizen testimony </I>
</CENTER>

<P>
The importance of tax reform to economic growth,
jobs and entrepreneurship will be the focus of a public hearing
in Cleveland, Ohio, on Wednesday, September 27, 1995, it was announced
today by Jack Kemp, chairman of the National Commission on Economic
Growth and Taxation.
<P>
The details of the hearing are:
<P>
Location: Ambassador Ballroom, Stouffer's Renaissance
Hotel, 24 Public Square, Cleveland
<P>
Time:  2:00 p.m. until 5:00 p.m., Wednesday, September
27
<P>
Witnesses: Among those confirmed are:
<ul>
<li>
  David Zanotti, President, Roundtables of Ohio
<li>
  Joseph P. Ditchman, Jr., President, Ohio Association
of Realtors
<li>
  Donald Korb, Chair, 1995 New Cleveland Tax Institute
<li>
  Lee Donaho, Executive Director, National Taxpayers
Union of Ohio
<li>
  Scott Cipinko, National Association of Life Companies
</ul>
<br>
Background: The Cleveland hearing is 12th and final
public hearing being held by the Tax Reform 
 Commission (TRC) in the three months since it was
formed.  More than 100 witnesses,  from all walks of American life, have testified
before the commission.
<P>
  The 14-member TRC was appointed by Senate Majority
Leader Bob Dole and House Speaker Newt Gingrich, who charged the commission
with making recommendations for a tax code that is &quot;flatter, fairer, and
simpler&quot; - a system that will encourage  economic growth and greater opportunity for all
Americans.  The commission plans to issue its final recommendations by the end of
1995.
<P>
  Besides Chairman Kemp, Commission members include
Edwin J. Feulner, Jr., President, The Heritage Foundation, Vice-Chairman of the Commission;
also, Loretta H. Adams, President, Market Development, Inc.; J. Kenneth
Blackwell, Ohio State Treasurer; Herman Cain, Chairman and CEO, Godfather's Pizza, Inc.;
Carroll Campbell, former Governor of South Carolina; Pete du Pont, former Governor
of Delaware and Policy Director, National Center for Policy Analysis; Jack Faris,
President, National Federation of Independent Business; Matt Fong, California State
Treasurer; Theodore J. Forstmann, Partner, Forstmann Little &amp; Co.; Dean R. Kleckner,
President, American Farm Bureau Federation; Shirley Peterson, President, Hood College
and former IRS Commissioner; John Snow, Chairman, President and CEO, CSX Corporation;
and John Wieland, President, John Wieland Homes, Inc.</blockquote><P>


<P><P><font size="-1"><a href="/taxcom/prindex.html">PR Index</a> | <a href="/taxcom/">TRC Home</a> | <a href="/taxcom/reptoc.html">The Report</a></font></center><P></body>

