<title>Public Hearing on "Compliance Costs and Burdens" -- TRC</title>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<center><i>July 10, 1995</i>
<P>
<h3>Public Hearing on &quot;Compliance Costs and Burdens&quot;</h3>
</CENTER>

<P>
<blockquote>WHAT: The National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform
is holding its second public hearing.  The subject is &quot;Compliance
Costs and Burdens.&quot; Commission Chairman Jack Kemp will introduce
expert witnesses and the members of the Tax Reform Commission
will engage in discussion and an exchange of ideas.
<P>
WHEN: Wednesday, July 12, 1995 from 9:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m.
<P>
WHERE: U.S. Chamber of Commerce
<br>
  1615 H Street, N.W.
<br>
  Washington, D.C.
<P>
WHY:  Senate leader Dole and House Speaker Gingrich have charged
the Tax Reform Commission with producing recommendations for a
tax system that is &quot;flatter, fairer and simpler.&quot;  The
Commission plans to conduct a series of hearings and will issue
its report in December.
<P>
WHO:  Chairman Jack Kemp and Tax Reform Commission Members, U.S.
Chamber of Commerce Representative, and expert witnesses.
<P>
ADDITIONAL NOTE:

  The Tax Reform Commission will hold its first Field Hearing
in Boston, Massachusetts on Wednesday, July 19, 1995 on &quot;The
Impact of the Tax System on Economic Growth and Tax Receipts.&quot;
 Details to be announced.
</bockquote>
