<title>Congress of the United States, Press Release</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><b><i>Congress of the United States<br>
Washington, DC 20515</center></b></i>
<p>
Wednesday, May 24, 1995
<p>
<center><h3>ECONOMIC GROWTH & TAX REFORM COMMISSION
GINGRICH & DOLE NAME MEMBERS</h3></center>
<p>
WASHINGTON -- House Speaker Newt Gingrich and Senate Majority
Leader Bob Dole today named 13 distinguished Americans to serve
on the National Commission on Economic Growth & Tax Reform,
chaired by Jack Kemp. The Commission was established April 3rd
by Gingrich and Dole to examine overhauling the tax system to
make it flatter, fairer, and simpler. The panel is expected to
make its recommendations to Gingrich & Dole later this year.
<p>
Named to the Commission were:
<p>
<dl>
<dt>Loretta Adams
<dd>Founder & President, San Diego-based Market Development, Inc.
<dt>Ken Blackwell
<dd>Ohio State Treasurer
<dt>Herman Cain
<dd>CEO, Godfather's Pizza; Former President, National Restaurant Association
<dt>Carroll Campbell
<dd>former Governor of South Carolina; former member House Ways & Means Committee; President & CEO, American Council of Life Insurance
<dt>Pete DuPont
<dd>Former Governor of Delaware; Policy Chairman, National Center for Policy Analysis
<dt>Jack Faris
<dd>President & CEO, National Federation of Independent Business
<dt>Ed Feulner
<dd>President, The Heritage Foundation
<dt>Matt Fong
<dd>California State Treasurer
<dt>Ted Forstmann
<dd>Partner, Forstmann-Little
<dt>Dean Kleckner
<dd>President, American Farm Bureau Federation
<dt>Shirley Peterson
<dd>Former IRS Commissioner; former Assistant Attorney General for the Tax Division; President-elect, Hood College, Frederick, MD
<dt>John Snow
<dd>CEO, CSX Corporation; Chairman, Business Roundtable
<dt>John Weiland
<dd>President, Weiland Homes, Inc
</dl>
<p>
<p>
Contacts:<br>
Tony Blankley (Gingrich) -- 202-225-2800<br>
Clarkson Hine (Dole) -- 202-224-5358
<p>
