<TITLE>EDWIN MEESE, III -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>EDWIN MEESE, III</H3>
<HR>
<B>RONALD REAGAN FELLOW IN PUBLIC POLICY</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/meese.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Former U.S. Attorney General Meese was among President Reagan's most important advisors. As Chairman of the Domestic Policy Council and the National Drug Policy Board and as a member of the National Security Council, he played a key role in the development and execution of domestic and foreign policy. During the 1970s, Meese was Director of the Center for Criminal Justice Policy and Management and Professor of Law at the University of San Diego. He earlier served  as  Chief of  Staff for then-Governor  Reagan  and was a local prosecutor in California. Meese also is a Distinguished Visiting Fellow at the Hoover Institution.

<BR><HR WIDTH="30%"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER></BODY>
