<html>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<title> Stephen Jerome Yates - Heritage</title>
<h3>Stephen Jerome Yates</h3>
<hr>
<b> Policy Analyst for China</b>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/yates.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
<P>


Yates specializes in U.S. policy toward China, Taiwan, and Hong Kong.  Previously a language analyst at the Department of Defense, he also worked at the Commerce Department in support of Secretary Brown's 1994 Business Development Mission to China.  Yates lived in Taiwan for two years as a missionary and is fluent in Mandarin.  A Maryland native, Yates earned his B.A. in Chinese at the University of Maryland at College Park and his M.A. in International Economics and China Studies from Johns Hopkins University SAIS.


<P><p><HR WIDTH="30%"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER></BODY>
