<html>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<TITLE>ROBERT O'QUINN -- Heritage Staff</TITLE>

<H3>ROBERT O'QUINN</H3>
<HR>
<B>POLICY ANALYST, INTERNATIONAL TRADE AND ECONOMICS</B>
<p><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/oquinn.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<p>
Robert P. O'Quinn is an economist with wide-ranging business, government, and political experience.  A specialist in international trade, investment, and monetary issues, O'Quinn can demonstrate the importance of free trade, especially with the Asia-Pacific region, to key audiences.
<p>
	O'Quinn is an expert on the World Trade Organization (WTO) and 1994 Uruguay Round Agreements.  He also is an expert on the 18-member forum for Asia-Pacific Cooperation (APEC), which is setting the agenda for trade and economic development in the entire Asia-Pacific region, and its plans for a free trade area by 2020.  He is knowledgeable about other regional trade initiatives in the Americas and Asia, including NAFTA and the ASEAN Free Trade Area.
<p>
	O'Quinn, formerly an economist at the Federal Trade Commission, can speak authoritatively on antitrust and competition policy issues.  Previously a financial analyst at the Federal Reserve Board and an officer at First Union, one of America's largest banking firms, O'Quinn can also speak on domestic financial regulation, monetary policy, international financial services and exchange rate issues.  
<p>
	O'Quinn is a specialist on the economies and politics of Australia, Japan, New Zealand, and Singapore.  He has his bachelor's and M.B.A. in monetary economics from the University of Georgia.

<p>
