<TITLE>DR. WILLIAM J. BENNETT -- Heritage </TITLE>
<H3>
DR. WILLIAM J. BENNETT</H3>
<B>DISTINGUISHED FELLOW, CULTURAL POLICY STUDIES</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/bennett.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Dr. Bennett, former U.S. Secretary of Education and National Drug Control Policy Director, examines how government policies and programs affect American culture, and in turn, how American culture affects government policies and programs.  Bennett is the author of the nationwide bestseller, The Book of Virtues (Simon & Schuster). A former Chairman of the National Endowment of the Humanities, Bennett serves as co-director of Empower America and a Senior Editor of National Review.  Bennett earned his Ph.D. from the University of Texas and his J.D. from Harvard University.

