<title>Policy Papers</title>

<body background="/townhall/FRC/images/bckgnd2.gif" text="#ff0000" 
vlink="#000000">

<center>
<h1><font size=+3>P</font>olicy <font size=+3>P</font>apers</h1>
</center>

<p>
<b>Many of FRC's papers, fact sheets and articles are released 
initially to opinion leaders in government, business, and the 
mass media. In turn, we make these materials available to the 
general public.
<p>
These materials are for your own benefit, so feel free to copy 
them, print them out or redistribute them to friends and family. 
However, if you plan on redisributing these materials for 
commercial reasons or if you want to quote these materials in 
other publications, please read 
<a href="/townhall/FRC/reproduce/reproduc.html">this</a> first.
<p>
If you would rather not browse through all of these materials, 
you can try using our <a href="/townhall/FRC/issues/issues.html">search 
engine</a> as well. This will help you find what you're looking 
for more quickly.</b>

<p>
<center><img src="/townhall/FRC/images/redline.gif"></center>
<p>

<center><h2>Publications Available</h2></center>

<p><dl>

<dt><h3><a href="/townhall/FRC/infocus/">In Focus</a></h3>
<dd><b><i>In Focus</i> papers provide &quot;talking points&quot; on 
specific issues. They are typically 1-3 pages in length and outline 
the basic facts and arguments of various issues.</b>

<p>

<dt><h3><a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/">Insight</a></h3>
<dd><b><i>Insight</i> papers offer a more in-depth look at a specific 
issue. They are analytical in nature and are typically 4 pages and 
longer.</b>

<p>

<dt><h3><a href="/townhall/FRC/perspective/">Perspective</a></h3>
<dd><b><i>Perspective</i> papers are &quot;op-ed&quot; in nature. 
They contain an author's opinion/view on a particular topic as 
well as offer factual information. They are typically 2-3 pages 
in length.</b>

<p>

<dt><h3><a href="/townhall/FRC/podium/">At the Podium</a></h3>
<dd><b><i>At the Podium</i> papers are transcripts, and at times, 
detailed notes of speeches and addresses given by FRC staff. 
However, not all speeches are published and printed.</b>

</dl>

<p>
<center><img src="/townhall/FRC/images/redline.gif"></center>
<p>

<center>
<a href="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrp2.map">
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/navstrp2.gif" ismap border="0"></a>
<br>

