<p>

<i>Insight</i> produces vital policy backgrounders on issues before
Congress, the administration or federal agencies.  <i>Insight</i> 
appears as the need arises, either to underline particular items of 
our agenda or to clarify our objections to something we oppose.  Each 
<i>Insight</i> offers policymakers clear and thorough analysis in a 
convenient format.  They are typically 4 pages and longer.

<p>

These <i>Insights</i> are for your own benefit, so feel free 
to copy them, print them out or redistribute them to friends and 
family. However, if you plan on redisributing these materials for 
commercial reasons or if you want to quote these materials in 
other publications, please read 
<font size=+1><a href="/townhall/FRC/reproduce/reproduc.html">this</a></font> 
first.

<p>

Also, if you have trouble finding what you're looking for, make sure 
to try our <font size=+1><a href="/townhall/FRC/issues/issues.html">search 
engine</a></font>. It will help you find the materials that you need.

<p>

1995 <i>Insight</i> publications are available 
<font size=+1><a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/1995.html">here</a></font>. 
Any documents prior to 1995 will be made available shortly. All 
<i>Insights</i> from this year are listed below.


