</ul>
<b>3/7/97</b>
<ul>
<Li>Michael Fumento takes on <a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0306.html">&quot;Sugar, The Everglades ... and Big Government&quot; </a> in his latest column. 
<li>Marvin Olasky details the right way to <a href="/heritage/p_review/mar96/olasky.html">replace welfare</a> in the lastest <i>Policy Review</i>.
<li>Do you believe that all of your savings and investments should be tax deductible and tax deferred until you, or your beneficiary, consume it? The Savers &amp; Investors League does; <a href="/savers/philos.html">find out more</a>. 

</ul> 
<b>3/6/96</b>
<ul>
<li><i>National Review</i> offers up a list of <a href="/nationalreview/11mar96/feature.html">100 best conservative movies</a>.
<li>Republican leaders, decrying "the looming Clinton recession," are crafting a <a href="/wash_times/news.3_4.html">legislative agenda
for the campaign year</a> that focuses on economic growth, jobs, incomes and some issues favored by social conservatives. Find out more in this week's <i>Washington Times National Weekly Edition</i>.
<li><a href="/heritage/p_review/mar96/wepeo.html">"Charities on the Dole"</a> by Kimberly Dennis, in the latest <i>Policy Review</i>.
