<li>Read Congressional testimony on <a href="/pff/congtest/ct092895.html">regulatory</a> policy from the Progress & Freedom Foundation.
<li>This week's Town Hall Spotlight focuses on our <a href="/townhall/spotlights/10-2-95/welcome.html">Citizen</a> Organizations. <a href="/townhall/spotlights/10-2-95/i-monday.html">Today</a> visit the sites on the James Madison line!
<li>"You Must Learn to <a href="/townhall/columnists/howl0926.html">Forgive</a>"...a column by Kathleen Howley.
<li>New columns by F.R. Duplantier: "The Anti-Ballistic <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0927.html">Missile</a> Treaty; and "Economic <a href="/townhall/columnists/dupl0928.html">Espionage</a>"

</ul>

<b>Updated 10/1/95</b><br>
<ul>
<li><a href="/heritage/commentary/op-gip1.html">"Lobbyists</a> Bring Scare Tactics to Your Hometown"...new commentary from The Heritage Foundation.
<li>Guest columnist, Michael Fumento, has two new columns: "New York Times Blows Hot Air Over <a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0921.html">Global Warming</a>" and "<a href="/townhall/columnists/fume0926.html">Racial Politics</a> Make Strange Politics." 
<li>Read National Review's week-end <a href="/nationalreview/daily/nr929.html">reports</a> on the CPI and Ross Perot.
</ul>
