<li>September 12, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav091296.html">Where's our moral outrage?</a>
<li>September 5, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav090596.html">Promises Don't Help Kids Read</a>
<li>August 28, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav082896.html">Dem's Use of the 'E-Word' Flies in Their Faces</a>
<li>August 21, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav082196.html">Perot's Legacy May Be Helping to Elect Clinton Twice</a>
<li>August 15, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav081496.html">GOP Gender Gap Simply "Hogwash"</a>
<li>August 2, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav080296.html">We're Becoming a Nation of Crybabies</a>
<li>July 24, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav072496.html">Space Exploration a Worthy Investment</a>
<li>July 8, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav070396.html">New Citizens Getting Off Too Easily</a>
<li>July 1, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav062696.html">FBI Files: Look What I Found In Mine</a>
<li>June 14, 1996 <a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/chav061296.html">Crazed Fans Become Sideline Guerrillas</a>

<p><a href="/townhall/columnists/chavez/">Archive</a>
</ul>
<p><br><p><br>

<center>
