<table>
<tr><td width="200"></td><td><td width="340"><P>
<FONT SIZE=3><P ALIGN=Center><B>Submission Policies</B></P><P>
    Anything related to conservative political interests is welcome on the C-News list, so long as it is not discussion. For example, we welcome:<p>

<LI>Policy reports or essays from conservative interest groups<P>
<LI>News items: Excerpts from newspapers/magazines of news that would not be 
available elsewhere or is a breaking story<P>
<LI>Information on election results and campaigns of conservative candidates<P>
<LI>Book reviews<P>
<LI>Announcements of upcoming events<P>


<hr>

<P ALIGN=Center><B>List Policies to Keep in Mind:</B></P><p>

-    Although in a list such as this posts may often be rather long, we 
 would ask that you post the complete text of something only if it is not 
 available elsewhere. For example, articles from _Policy Review_ are  
 available via WWW at <a href="http://townhall.com/">Town Hall</a>. Instead of          
 posting an entire article, post a citation and information on how to get the  
 article.<p>

-  Also, we would ask that complete posts from C-News not be cross-posted; 
 C-News has been established to eliminate the need for cross-posting. 
 However, there is no problem with forwarding excerpts for discussion 
 purposes.<p>

-  PLEASE do not forward C-News posts to the White House, the media or to 
 Congressional offices. When you do that, all that happens is a.)the
 message gets deleted by whoever receives it, and b.)the person who
 posted the message to C-News gets bombarded with "Thank you for
 your comments..." messages from the offices.<p>

-  If you want to scan something in to post to C-News, be sure to 
 edit it for scanning errors and layout problems. Posts that are
 scanned and have excessive errors <B>will not</B> be accepted.<p>

-  Finally, have fun!<p>
	    </FONT>

